<leg:heading><desig searchtype="PART-NUM"><designum><refpt id="UCPN.OL.ADR88.PT4" type="ext"/>PART IV</designum></desig><title searchtype="PART-TITLE">PROCESS [rr 18&#x2013;29]</title></leg:heading>
<leg:levelbody>
<leg:level id="UCPN.OL.ADR88.PT4.D1"><leg:level-vrnt leveltype="division" searchtype="LEGISLATION DIVISION" subdoc="false" toc-caption="DIVISION 1 INITIATING PROCESS [rr 18&#x2013;21]">
<leg:heading><desig searchtype="DIV-NUM"><designum><refpt id="UCPN.OL.ADR88.PT4.D1" type="ext"/>DIVISION 1</designum></desig><title searchtype="DIV-TITLE">INITIATING PROCESS [rr 18&#x2013;21]</title></leg:heading>
<leg:levelbody>
<leg:level id="UCPN.OL.ADR88.R18"><leg:level-vrnt leveltype="rul" searchtype="LEGISLATION RUL" subdoc="true" toc-caption="[255,280] r 18 Separate commencement of in rem and in personam actions">
<leg:levelinfo>
<leg:levelstatus isrepealed="false" ln.user-displayed="false"/></leg:levelinfo>
<leg:heading inline="true"><edpnum><refpt id="UCPN.OL.ADR88.R18" type="ext"/>[255,280]</edpnum><title searchtype="RUL-TITLE">Separate commencement of <emph typestyle="it">in rem</emph> and <emph typestyle="it">in personam</emph> actions</title><desig searchtype="RUL-NUM"><designum>18</designum></desig></leg:heading>
<leg:levelbody>
<leg:bodytext>
<p><text>A proceeding commenced as an action <emph typestyle="it">in personam</emph> must not be commenced by the same initiating process as the process by which a proceeding is commenced as an action <emph typestyle="it">in rem</emph>.</text></p>
<leg:histnote>
<p><text>[r 16  am SR 287 of 2006 r 3 and Sch 1.37, effective 18 November 2006]</text></p></leg:histnote>
</leg:bodytext>
</leg:levelbody>
</leg:level-vrnt>
</leg:level>
<leg:level id="UCPN.OL.ADR88.R19"><leg:level-vrnt leveltype="rul" searchtype="LEGISLATION RUL" subdoc="true" toc-caption="[255,285] r 19 Initiating process">
<leg:levelinfo>
<leg:levelstatus isrepealed="false" ln.user-displayed="false"/></leg:levelinfo>
<leg:heading inline="true"><edpnum><refpt id="UCPN.OL.ADR88.R19" type="ext"/>[255,285]</edpnum><title searchtype="RUL-TITLE">Initiating process</title><desig searchtype="RUL-NUM"><designum>19</designum></desig></leg:heading>
<leg:levelbody>
<leg:bodytext>
<p><text>A proceeding commenced as an action <emph typestyle="it">in rem</emph> must be commenced by writ in accordance with 
<ci:cite searchtype="LEG-REF"><ci:content><remotelink dpsi="05CC" refpt="UCPN.OL.ADR88.SCH1.F6" remotekey1="REFPTID" service="DOC-ID">Form 6 </remotelink></ci:content></ci:cite>
.</text></p>
<leg:histnote>
<p><text>[r 19  am SR 287 of 2006 r 3 and Sch 1.37, effective 18 November 2006]</text></p></leg:histnote>
<leg:comntry subdoc="true" toc-caption="NOTE"><heading searchtype="COMMENTARY"><title><refpt id="UCPN.OL.ADR88.R19.COM1" type="ext"/>NOTE</title></heading>
<level id="UCPN_OL.SGM_UCPN.OL.255285-5" leveltype="para0" subdoc="true" toc-caption="[255,285.5]"><heading searchtype="COMMENTARY"><edpnum><refpt id="UCPN.OL.255285-5" type="ext"/>[255,285.5] </edpnum></heading>
<bodytext searchtype="COMMENTARY">
<p>
<text>No specific provision is made in the rules for the commencement of proceedings <emph typestyle="it">in personam</emph>. The former practice of the court was that they were commenced by ordinary statement of claim. Under the Uniform Civil Procedure Rules 2005 proceedings will be commenced by Summons. </text></p>
</bodytext>
</level></leg:comntry>
</leg:bodytext>
</leg:levelbody>
</leg:level-vrnt>
</leg:level>
<leg:level id="UCPN.OL.ADR88.R20"><leg:level-vrnt leveltype="rul" searchtype="LEGISLATION RUL" subdoc="true" toc-caption="[255,290] r 20 Validity of initiating process">
<leg:levelinfo>
<leg:levelstatus isrepealed="false" ln.user-displayed="false"/></leg:levelinfo>
<leg:heading inline="true"><edpnum><refpt id="UCPN.OL.ADR88.R20" type="ext"/>[255,290]</edpnum><title searchtype="RUL-TITLE">Validity of initiating process</title><desig searchtype="RUL-NUM"><designum>20</designum></desig></leg:heading>
<leg:levelbody>
<leg:bodytext>
<p><text>Initiating process in a proceeding commenced as an action <emph typestyle="it">in rem</emph> is effective for service for a period of 12 months after it is issued and may not be served after that time without the leave of the court.</text></p>
<leg:comntry subdoc="true" toc-caption="NOTE"><heading searchtype="COMMENTARY"><title><refpt id="UCPN.OL.ADR88.R20.COM1" type="ext"/>NOTE</title></heading>
<level id="UCPN_OL.SGM_UCPN.OL.255290-5" leveltype="para0" subdoc="true" toc-caption="[255,290.5] Renewal of writ">
<glp:note><blockquote><hrule/>
<p>
<text><inlineobject attachment="web-server" filename="leg1.gif" type="image"/> Legislation cited in [255,290.5] below. LawNow subscribers click through for daily updates and historical versions.</text><text> </text>
<text>(NSW) <ci:cite searchtype="LEG-REF"><ci:content><remotelink alttext="Click to link to LawNow Legislation" dpsi="005Y" refpt="NSW_REG_1970-1" remotekey1="REFPTID" service="DOC-ID">Supreme Court Rules 1970</remotelink> Pt 7 r 7.</ci:content></ci:cite></text>
</p></blockquote></glp:note><heading searchtype="COMMENTARY"><edpnum><refpt id="UCPN.OL.255290-5" type="ext"/>[255,290.5] </edpnum><title>Renewal of writ</title></heading>
<bodytext searchtype="COMMENTARY">
<p>
<text>The court has a wide discretion to renew a writ after its expiry, even if the limitation period has expired. Factors which the court may consider in deciding whether to grant leave include the length of, and reasons for, the delay and whether any notice was given to the defendant: <ci:cite searchtype="CASE-REF"><ci:case><ci:caseinfo><ci:decisiondate year="1981"/></ci:caseinfo><ci:caseref ID="cr000073" spanref="cr000073-001"><ci:reporter value="ALR"/><ci:volume num="34"/><ci:page num="3"/></ci:caseref></ci:case><ci:content><citefragment searchtype="CASE-NAME-REF"><emph typestyle="it">Van Leer Australia Pty Ltd v Palace Shipping KK</emph></citefragment><citefragment searchtype="CASE-CITE-REF"> <ci:span spanid="cr000073-001">(1981) 34 ALR 3</ci:span></citefragment> <remotelink dpsi="0018" refpt="77641" remotekey1="REFPTID" service="DOC-ID"><inlineobject alttext="Click for CaseBase entry" attachment="web-server" filename="cbcc.gif" type="image"/></remotelink></ci:content></ci:cite>; see also the provisions in 
<ci:cite searchtype="LEG-REF"><ci:content><remotelink dpsi="05CC" refpt="UCPN.SC.SCR70.PT7.R7" remotekey1="REFPTID" service="DOC-ID" status="unval">Pt 7 r 7</remotelink></ci:content></ci:cite>
 and the notes thereto.</text></p>
</bodytext>
</level></leg:comntry>
</leg:bodytext>
</leg:levelbody>
</leg:level-vrnt>
</leg:level>
<leg:level id="UCPN.OL.ADR88.R21"><leg:level-vrnt leveltype="rul" searchtype="LEGISLATION RUL" subdoc="true" toc-caption="[255,295] r 21 Limitation proceedings">
<leg:levelinfo>
<leg:levelstatus isrepealed="false" ln.user-displayed="false"/></leg:levelinfo>
<leg:heading inline="true"><edpnum><refpt id="UCPN.OL.ADR88.R21" type="ext"/>[255,295]</edpnum><title searchtype="RUL-TITLE">Limitation proceedings</title><desig searchtype="RUL-NUM"><designum>21</designum></desig></leg:heading>
<leg:levelbody>
<leg:level id="UCPN.OL.ADR88.R21.1"><leg:level-vrnt leveltype="subrul" searchtype="LEGISLATION SUBRUL">
<leg:levelinfo>
<leg:levelstatus isrepealed="false" ln.user-displayed="false"/></leg:levelinfo>
<leg:heading inline="true"><desig><designum><refpt id="UCPN.OL.ADR88.R21.1" type="ext"/>(1)</designum></desig></leg:heading>
<leg:levelbody>
<leg:bodytext>
<p><text>A limitation proceeding must be commenced as an action <emph typestyle="it">in personam</emph>.</text></p>
<leg:histnote>
<p><text>[subr (1)  am SR 287 of 2006 r 3 and Sch 1.37, effective 18 November 2006]</text></p></leg:histnote>
</leg:bodytext>
</leg:levelbody>
</leg:level-vrnt>
</leg:level>
<leg:level id="UCPN.OL.ADR88.R21.2"><leg:level-vrnt leveltype="subrul" searchtype="LEGISLATION SUBRUL">
<leg:levelinfo>
<leg:levelstatus isrepealed="false" ln.user-displayed="false"/></leg:levelinfo>
<leg:heading inline="true"><desig><designum><refpt id="UCPN.OL.ADR88.R21.2" type="ext"/>(2)</designum></desig></leg:heading>
<leg:levelbody>
<leg:bodytext>
<p><text>A limitation proceeding must be commenced by a statement of claim in accordance with 
<ci:cite searchtype="LEG-REF"><ci:content><remotelink dpsi="05CC" refpt="UCPN.OL.ADR88.SCH1.F7" remotekey1="REFPTID" service="DOC-ID">Form 7</remotelink></ci:content></ci:cite>
.</text></p>
<leg:histnote>
<p><text>[subr (2)  am SR 287 of 2006 r 3 and Sch 1.37, effective 18 November 2006]</text></p></leg:histnote>
</leg:bodytext>
</leg:levelbody>
</leg:level-vrnt>
</leg:level>
<leg:level id="UCPN.OL.ADR88.R21.3"><leg:level-vrnt leveltype="subrul" searchtype="LEGISLATION SUBRUL">
<leg:levelinfo>
<leg:levelstatus isrepealed="false" ln.user-displayed="false"/></leg:levelinfo>
<leg:heading inline="true"><desig><designum><refpt id="UCPN.OL.ADR88.R21.3" type="ext"/>(3)</designum></desig></leg:heading>
<leg:levelbody>
<leg:bodytext>
<p><text>At least 1 of the respondents to the limitation proceeding must be named as respondent in the initiating process.</text></p>
<leg:histnote>
<p><text>[subr (3)  am SR 287 of 2006 r 3 and Sch 1.37, effective 18 November 2006]</text></p></leg:histnote>
</leg:bodytext>
</leg:levelbody>
</leg:level-vrnt>
</leg:level>
<leg:level id="UCPN.OL.ADR88.R21.4"><leg:level-vrnt leveltype="subrul" searchtype="LEGISLATION SUBRUL">
<leg:levelinfo>
<leg:levelstatus isrepealed="false" ln.user-displayed="false"/></leg:levelinfo>
<leg:heading inline="true"><desig><designum><refpt id="UCPN.OL.ADR88.R21.4" type="ext"/>(4)</designum></desig></leg:heading>
<leg:levelbody>
<leg:bodytext>
<p><text>Other respondents need not be so named but may be identified as respondents in the initiating process by reference to their being members of a specified class of persons.</text></p>
</leg:bodytext>
</leg:levelbody>
</leg:level-vrnt>
</leg:level>
<leg:level id="UCPN.OL.ADR88.R21.5"><leg:level-vrnt leveltype="subrul" searchtype="LEGISLATION SUBRUL">
<leg:levelinfo>
<leg:levelstatus isrepealed="false" ln.user-displayed="false"/></leg:levelinfo>
<leg:heading inline="true"><desig><designum><refpt id="UCPN.OL.ADR88.R21.5" type="ext"/>(5)</designum></desig></leg:heading>
<leg:levelbody>
<leg:bodytext>
<p><text>Initiating process need not be served on respondents so identified.</text></p>
</leg:bodytext>
</leg:levelbody>
</leg:level-vrnt>
</leg:level>
<leg:bodytext>
<leg:comntry subdoc="true" toc-caption="NOTE"><heading searchtype="COMMENTARY"><title><refpt id="UCPN.OL.ADR88.R21.COM1" type="ext"/>NOTE</title></heading>
